headline: Kenvue forecasts annual profit below estimates amid strategic review
summary: Wall Street analysts view the Band-Aid maker as an acquisition target after it came under pressure from investors, who have criticized the lackluster performance in its skin health and beauty segment that houses brands such as Neutrogena and Aveeno.  Kenvue in July ousted its CEO Thibaut Mongon and named Kirk Perry as an interim chief, and had then said it created a committee to weigh portfolio simplification and potential divestitures.
